### Description

When using a pipe multiple times in the HTML template of a component, a new pipe instance is created for each occurrence. Here’s an example to illustrate this behavior:

```ts
import { Component, PipeTransform, Pipe } from '@angular/core';
import { bootstrapApplication } from '@angular/platform-browser';

@Pipe({
  name: 'myPipe',
  standalone: true,
})
export class MyPipe implements PipeTransform {
  constructor() {
    console.log('MyPipe');
  }

  transform(value: string) {
    return value.toLowerCase();
  }
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [MyPipe],
  template: `
    {{ 'Hello' | myPipe }}
    {{ 'Hello' | myPipe }}
    {{ 'Hello' | myPipe }}
    {{ 'Hello' | myPipe }}
  `,
})
export class App {}

bootstrapApplication(App);
```

The console output for this example is:
```
MyPipe
MyPipe
MyPipe
MyPipe
```

This behavior has a performance impact when the pipe involves initialization logic or injects services. For example, consider a pipe that performs expensive computations during its construction.


### Proposed solution

Introduce an option in the `@Pipe` decorator to specify that the pipe should be treated as a **singleton** within the template. This could work like this:

```ts
import { Component, PipeTransform, Pipe } from '@angular/core';
import { bootstrapApplication } from '@angular/platform-browser';

@Pipe({
  name: 'myPipe',
  standalone: true,
  singleton: true // <---- Ensures only one instance per template
})
export class MyPipe implements PipeTransform {
  constructor() {
    console.log('MyPipe');
  }

  transform(value: string) {
    return value.toLowerCase();
  }
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [MyPipe],
  template: `
    {{ 'Hello' | myPipe }}
    {{ 'Hello' | myPipe }}
    {{ 'Hello' | myPipe }}
    {{ 'Hello' | myPipe }}
  `,
})
export class App {}

bootstrapApplication(App);
```

With this change, the console output would become:
```
MyPipe
```

This ensures only one instance of the pipe is created per template, reducing unnecessary overhead while maintaining the current behavior for pipes where multiple instances are desired.

### Alternatives considered

```ts
@Pipe({
  name: 'myPipe',
  standalone: true,
  provideInTemplate: true // <---- Ensures only one instance per template
})
```

